The article discusses the 70th anniversary of the Lavender Scare, a period in American history when LGBTQI+ Americans were banned from serving in the Federal Government. The article highlights the discrimination and persecution faced by LGBTQI+ federal employees during this time, as well as the bravery of activists who fought for their rights. It also acknowledges the progress made in advancing LGBTQI+ equality in recent years, including the appointment of LGBTQI+ leaders in government and the signing of executive orders to protect LGBTQI+ rights. The article emphasizes the need to continue fighting against discrimination and supporting LGBTQI+ Americans. Finally, President Biden proclaims April 27, 2023, as the 70th Anniversary of the Lavender Scare and calls upon the nation to honor the contributions of LGBTQI+ public servants and celebrate the diversity of the American people.